{"lemma":"رَواحِ","slug":"رَواحِ","root":"ر.#.ح","root_slug":"ر-_-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-_-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رَواح","root":"روح","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16997","n17007"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AD%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَاحَ (rāḥa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"evening, time between sunset and night","examples":[{"text":"يَا أَبَا ذَر: مَا مِن صَبَاحٍ وَلَا رَوَاحٍ إِلَّا وَبِقَاع الَارْضِ يُنَادِي بَعْضَهَا بَعْضَا","english":"Oh Abu Dharr! No morning or evening pass without every corner on earth calling one another. (part of a Hadith)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"evening journey","examples":[{"text":"Coordinate term: غُدُوّ (ḡuduww)"},{"text":"وَلِسُلَيْمَـٰنَ ٱلرِّيحَ غُدُوُّهَا شَهْرٌۭ وَرَوَاحُهَا شَهْرٌۭ ۖ","english":"And to Solomon ˹We subjected˺ the wind: its morning stride was a month’s journey and so was its evening stride."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of رَاحَ (rāḥa)."},"ipa":["/ra.waːħ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16997","headword_ar":"رَوَاحٌ","root":"rwH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAHapN","text_ar":"رَاحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b2-  It is also an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAHa","text_ar":"رَاحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [q. v.,] signifying the contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guduwN","text_ar":"غُدُوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b3-  And it signifies also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evening;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"afternoon, from the declining of the sun from the meridian until night."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAruwA rawaAHFA","text_ar":"سَارُوا رَوَاحًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They journeyed in the evening,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"afternoon"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiytuhu raAy^iHapF","text_ar":"لَقِيتُهُ رَايِحَةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I met him in the evening,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"afternoon."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarajowA","text_ar":"خَرَجْوا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"birawaAHK mina AlEa$iY~i","text_ar":"بِرَوَاحٍ مِنَ العَشِىِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn AlE$Y~","text_ar":"من العشىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biriyaAHK","text_ar":"بِرِيَاحٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the T, A, L, and K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"birayaAHK","text_ar":"بِرَيَاحٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn AlE$Y~","text_ar":"من العشىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA^arowaAHK","text_ar":"بِاَرْوَاحٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,) using a pl. form, (TA,) meaning the same, (S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They went forth in the beginning of the evening,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when there were yet some remains of the evening."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ataY fulaAnN wa Ealayohi mina Aln~ahaAri","text_ar":"اَتَى فُلَانٌ وَ عَلَيْهِ مِنَ النَّهَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyaAHN","text_ar":"رِيَاحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arowanHN","text_ar":"اَرْوَنحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one came when there were yet some remains for him of day"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","A","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n17007","headword_ar":"رَوَّاحٌ","root":"rwH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Very brisk, lively, sprightly, active, agile, prompt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAy^iHN","text_ar":"رَايِحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}